Label16.Text
data.value:
Thanks for downloading and using Medal of Honor HitFixer 2. The purpose of this program is to fix (or at least try to fix) the hit registration problems which afflict Medal of Honor and previous games from DICE.
If you've downloaded this program and you're using it then most likely you're experiencing problems with the netcode. You should not consider MOH_HF2 as a total fix for the hit registration, it'll just limit the cases of bad registration.
Why it can't be consider as a total fix? Because there are too many factors to take in consideration , like your connection and the enemies one. For sure you'll see an impovment but you still can have some fails.
Remember this program is completely free and was made during the free time by a no-professional programmer, so you may find some bugs in it. If you find any please report them to the creator.
Medal of Honor HitFixer 2 is made by Andrea 'Dendari' Marini based on Battlefield 2/21242 HitFixer. Credits go to Guy.Buddy.Friend from BF2S forums.
Dendari, 2012.
